    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/2605.15749v1</id>
    <title>Constraints on primordial black holes from the first part of LIGO-Virgo-KAGRA fourth observing run</title>
    <updated>2026-05-15T09:07:39Z</updated>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.15749v1" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2605.15749v1" rel="related" type="application/pdf" title="pdf"/>
    <summary>We analyze PBH populations using state-of-the-art modeling of PBH binaries, deriving the strongest bounds on PBH abundance in the $0.6-100 M_\odot$ range from LIGO-Virgo-KAGRA O4a data and demonstrating sensitivity in the $10^{-4}-10^4 M_\odot$ range. The constraints are dominated by resolvable PBH mergers, while the associated gravitational wave background provides complementary but weaker limits. Allowing PBHs to account for a subset of the cataloged events slightly relaxes these bounds. However, a joint fit with astrophysical black holes shows no compelling evidence for a PBH contribution.</summary>
